OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FGovernment to repeal law   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fallowing police to arrest  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Frough sleepers             
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The government has announced it will   
OL,6, repeal the Vagrancy Act, which allows  
OL,7, police to arrest people for sleeping   
OL,8, rough or begging in England and Wales. 
OL,10,FCurrently anyone convicted under the   
OL,11,Flaw faces a fine of up to #1,000 and a 
OL,12,Ftwo-year criminal record.              
OL,14,FHowever, ministers have now introduced 
OL,15,Fan amendment to a bill in Parliament   
OL,16,Fwhich scraps the law.                  
OL,18,FRough sleeping minister Eddie Hughes   
OL,19,Fsaid the law was "outdated and needs   
OL,20,Freplacing".                            
